 Here we have five-fifths to the third power times four-fifths to the third power. Both the factors have three of the same factors, so we can put them together and simplify to $\left(\frac{5}{7}\cdot\frac{4}{5}\right)^3$ . Then, we can reduce the expression to $\left(\frac{4}{7}\right)^{3}$ . Now we have
\begin{align*}
\left(\frac{5}{7}\right)^{3}\left(\frac{4}{5}\right)^{3}&=\left(\frac{4}{7}\right)^{3}\qquad\text{[Combine]}\\
&=\frac{64}{343}\qquad\qquad\text{[Simplify]} \\
\end{align*}
Answer: $\frac{64}{343}$

